11 Sec. 10. Section 54-191, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
12 amended to read:
13 54-191 (1) The Nebraska Brand Committee is hereby created.
14 (2) This subsection applies until subsection (3) of this section
15 applies. The Beginning August 28, 2007, the brand committee shall consist
16 of five members appointed by the Governor, subject to confirmation by the
17 Legislature. At least three appointed members shall be active
18 cattlepersons and at least one appointed member shall be an active cattle
19 feeder. The Secretary of State and the Director of Agriculture, or their
20 designees, shall be nonvoting, ex officio members of the brand committee.
21 The appointed members shall be owners of cattle within the brand
22 inspection area, shall reside within the brand inspection area, shall be
23 owners of Nebraska-recorded brands, and shall be persons whose principal
24 business and occupation is the raising or feeding of cattle within the
25 brand inspection area.
26 (3) This subsection applies beginning on August 28, 2026. The brand
27 committee shall consist of:
28 (a) The following seven voting members who are appointed by the
29 Governor and subject to confirmation by the Legislature:
30 (i) One person who resides in brand committee district one and whose
31 principal business or occupation is the raising of cattle;
