1 registrations, and official acts shall be kept.
2 (2) The brand committee shall appoint employ an executive director
3 who shall be the brand committee head for administrative purposes. The
4 appointment shall be subject to the approval of the Governor. The
5 executive director shall keep a record of all proceedings, transactions,
6 communications, and official acts of the brand committee, shall be
7 custodian of all records of the brand committee, and shall perform such
8 other duties as may be required by the brand committee. The executive
9 director shall call a meeting at the direction of the chairperson of the
10 brand committee, or in his or her absence the vice-chairperson, or upon
11 the written request of two or more members of the brand committee. The
12 executive director shall have supervisory authority to direct and control
13 all full-time and part-time employees of the brand committee. This
14 authority allows the executive director to hire employees as are needed
15 on an interim basis subject to approval or confirmation by the brand
16 committee for regular employment. The executive director may place
17 employees on probation and may discharge an employee.
18 (3) The brand committee shall employ a chief investigator who shall
19 report to the executive director. The chief investigator shall meet the
20 qualifications of an investigator as defined in section 54-182. Under the
21 direction of the executive director, the chief investigator shall be
22 chief of field operations and supervise brand committee investigators and
23 inspectors.
24 (4) The brand committee shall employ a brand recorder who shall be
25 responsible for the processing of all applications for new livestock
26 brands, the transfer of ownership of existing livestock brands, the
27 maintenance of accurate and permanent records relating to livestock
28 brands, and such other duties as may be required by the brand committee.
29 (5) If any employee of the brand committee after having been
30 disciplined, placed on probation, or having had his or her services
31 terminated desires to have a hearing before the entire brand committee,
-6-

AM3037 AM3037
LB1187 LB1187
