10 54-1,102 (1) A recorded brand may be applied by its owner until its
11 expiration date.
12 (2) On and after January 1, 1994, the expiration date of a recorded
13 brand is the last day of the calendar quarter of the renewal year as
14 designated by the Nebraska Brand Committee in the records of the brand
15 committee.
16 (3) The brand committee shall notify every owner of a recorded brand
17 of its expiration date at least sixty days prior to the expiration date,
18 and the owner of the recorded brand shall pay a renewal fee established
19 by the brand committee which shall not be more than four two hundred
20 dollars and furnish such other information as may be required by the
21 brand committee. The renewal fee is due and payable on or before the
22 expiration date and renews a recorded brand for a period of four years
23 regardless of the number of locations on one side of an animal on which
24 the brand is recorded. If any owner fails, refuses, or neglects to pay
25 the renewal fee by the expiration date, the brand shall expire and be
26 forfeited.
27 (4) The brand committee has the authority to hold an expired brand
28 for one year following the date of expiration. An expired brand may be
29 reinstated by the same owner during such one-year period upon return of a
30 brand application form and payment of the renewal fee recording fee and
31 research fee for such brand established by the brand committee under this
