14 certificate of inspection or brand clearance has been issued by the
15 Nebraska Brand Committee. Any person selling such cattle shall present to
16 the brand inspector a properly executed bill of sale, brand clearance, or
17 other satisfactory evidence of ownership which shall be filed with the
18 original certificate of inspection in the records of the brand committee.
19 Any time a brand inspection is required by law, a brand investigator or
20 brand inspector may transfer evidence of ownership of such cattle from a
21 seller to a purchaser by issuing a certificate of inspection.
22 (2) A brand inspection is not required:
23 (a) For cattle of a registered feedlot that are registered under
