30 subjected to brand inspection upon entering the originating backgrounding
31 lot.
-16-

AM3037 AM3037
LB1187 LB1187
MJP - 03/31/2026 MJP - 03/31/2026
1 (2) Cattle that are moved into a registered feedlot or a
2 backgrounding lot and that are not described in subsection (1) of this
3 section shall be subject to physical inspection or electronic inspection
4 within a reasonable time after arrival at the registered feedlot or
5 backgrounding lot. The inspection fee and surcharge that is provided
6 under section 54-1,108 shall be collected by the brand inspector at the
7 time that the inspection is performed.
8 (3) The brand committee may issue guidelines for processes of and
9 recordkeeping by backgrounding lots that may be used by backgrounding
10 lots to prevent the commingling of cattle during transport to such
11 backgrounding lots and to identify cattle that have become commingled
12 during transport to such backgrounding lots.
13 Any cattle originating in a state that has a brand inspection agency
14 and which are accompanied by a certificate of inspection or brand
15 clearance issued by such agency may be moved directly from the point of
16 origin into a registered feedlot. Any cattle not accompanied by such a
17 certificate of inspection or brand clearance or by satisfactory evidence
18 of ownership from states or portions of states not having brand
19 inspection shall be subjected to physical inspection for brands by the
20 Nebraska Brand Committee or, if applicable, subjected to electronic
21 inspection, within a reasonable time after arrival at a registered
22 feedlot, and the inspection fee and mileage charge, if applicable,
23 provided under section 54-1,108 shall be collected by the brand inspector
24 at the time the inspection is performed.
25 Sec. 18. (1) Any person, who operates a dairy heifer development
26 facility that specializes in the raising and managing of dairy heifers
27 from one day of age until such heifers are ready for entry into a
28 qualified dairy, may apply to the brand committee for registration as a
29 registered dairy heifer development facility. The application form shall
30 be prescribed by the brand committee and shall be made available by the
31 executive director of the brand committee for this purpose upon written
-17-

AM3037 AM3037
LB1187 LB1187
MJP - 03/31/2026 MJP - 03/31/2026
1 request.
2 (2) After the brand committee has received a properly completed
3 application, an agent of the brand committee shall within thirty days
4 make an investigation to determine if the facility is suitable for
5 licensing as a registered dairy heifer development facility and the
6 operator specializes in the raising and managing of dairy heifers from
7 one day of age until such heifers are ready for entry into a qualified
8 dairy.
9 (3) If the application is satisfactory, and upon payment of the
10 registration fee by the applicant, the brand committee shall issue a
11 registration number and registration certificate that are valid for one
12 year unless rescinded for cause by the brand committee. If the
13 registration is rescinded for cause, any registration fee shall be
14 forfeited by the applicant.
15 (4) The registration fee for a registered dairy heifer development
16 facility shall be an amount equal to fifty cents multiplied by the
17 maximum capacity of the facility, as such capacity is authorized by the
18 Department of Water, Energy, and Environment under the Livestock Waste
19 Management Act. The registration fee shall be paid on an annual basis.
20 Sec. 19. (1)(a) The brand committee shall audit each registered
21 dairy heifer development facility on at least three occasions during each
22 calendar year.
23 (b) Registered dairy heifer development facilities are subject to
24 audit at any reasonable time at the discretion of the brand committee and
25 its authorized agents, and the operator shall show cattle purchase
26 records or certificates of inspection to cover all cattle in his or her
27 facility. Cattle having originated from such registered dairy heifer
28 development facilities may from time to time, at the discretion of the
29 committee, be subject to a spot-check inspection and audit at destination
30 to enable the brand committee to assure satisfactory compliance with the
31 brand laws by the registered dairy heifer development facility operator.
-18-

AM3037 AM3037
LB1187 LB1187
MJP - 03/31/2026 MJP - 03/31/2026
1 (c) An audit shall not be performed under this subsection without
2 the prior approval of the brand committee.
3 (2) The operator of a registered dairy heifer development facility
4 shall keep cattle inventory records. The brand committee and its
5 employees may from time to time make spot checks and audits of the
6 registered dairy heifer development facilities and the records of cattle
7 on feed in such facilities.
8 Sec. 20. (1) Cattle that are sold or shipped from a registered
9 dairy heifer development facility, for purposes other than entry into a
10 qualified dairy, are subject to the brand inspection under sections
11 54-1,110 to 54-1,119, and the seller or shipper shall bear the cost of
12 such inspection at the regular fee.
13 (2) Any cattle that are not described in subsection (1) of this
14 section and that shipped from a registered dairy heifer development
15 facility or qualified dairy are not subject to brand inspection at origin
16 or destination, but the shipper shall have a shipping certificate from
17 the registered dairy heifer development facility or qualified dairy. The
18 shipping certificate form shall be prescribed by the brand committee and
19 shall show the registered dairy heifer development facility or qualified
20 dairy operator's name and registration number, date shipped, destination,
21 agency receiving the cattle, number of head in the shipment, and sex of
22 the cattle. The shipping certificate shall be completed in triplicate by
23 the registered dairy heifer development facility or qualified dairy
24 operator at the time of shipment. One copy thereof shall be delivered to
25 the brand inspector at the market along with shipment, if applicable, one
26 copy shall be sent to the brand committee by the tenth day of the
27 following month, and one copy shall be retained by the registered dairy
28 heifer development facility or qualified dairy operator. If a shipping
29 certificate does not accompany a shipment of cattle from a registered
30 dairy heifer development facility or qualified dairy to any destination
31 where brand inspection is maintained by the brand committee, all such
-19-

AM3037 AM3037
LB1187 LB1187
MJP - 03/31/2026 MJP - 03/31/2026
1 cattle shall be subject to a brand inspection and the inspection fees and
2 surcharge provided under section 54-1,108 shall be charged for the
3 service.
4 Sec. 21. Any cattle that originate in a state with a brand
5 inspection agency and that are accompanied by a certificate of inspection
6 or brand clearance issued by such agency may be moved directly from the
7 point of origin into a registered dairy heifer development facility or
8 qualified dairy. Any cattle not accompanied by such a certificate of
9 inspection or brand clearance or by satisfactory evidence of ownership
10 from states or portions of states that do not have brand inspection shall
11 be subjected to physical inspection for brands by the brand committee or,
12 if applicable, subjected to electronic inspection, within a reasonable
13 time after arrival at a registered dairy heifer development facility or
14 qualified dairy, and the inspection fee and mileage charge, if
15 applicable, provided under section 54-1,108 shall be collected by the
16 brand inspector at the time the inspection is performed.
17 Sec. 22. The brand committee may rescind the registration of any
18 registered dairy heifer development facility operator who (1) violates
19 sections 18 to 23 of this act, (2) fails to cooperate with the brand
20 committee or any employee of the brand committee who is acting in the
21 capacity of the brand committee, or (3) violates the rules and
22 regulations of the brand committee covering registered dairy heifer
23 development facilities.
24 Sec. 23. The brand committee may adopt and promulgate rules and
25 regulations to ensure compliance with the Livestock Brand Act by
26 registered dairy heifer development facilities, to provide for the
27 availability of shipping certificates to registered dairy heifer
28 development facilities, and to ensure that proper records are maintained
29 by registered dairy heifer development facilities.
30 Sec. 24. Sections 18 to 23 of this act shall not be construed to
31 prohibit the operation of nonqualified dairies.
